g.data-name: SEPT 2012: Police officer Mohammad Norazzuan Ahmad Zahari arrested at an unspecified location in Kedah in possession of 18 live pangolins.
NOV 2014: Police officer Mohammad Norazzuan Ahmad Zahari arrested again at the Bukit Kayu Hitam border checkpoint 43 live pangolins found in the boot of his car.
SEPT 2018: A police officer arrested with 81 live pangolins in a house rented under his name. The trial is ongoing.
FEB 2019: Police officer Ahmad Nasrul Hafifi Mohamad arrested at Sadao customs checkpoint with 47 pangolins in his car after passing Malaysian border checks.

All three officers worked at the Kedah state police headquarters IPK Kedah . Investigations suggest that there is a larger smuggling ring run by members of the police and officers from other enforcement agencies.
